1. The 20 Core DSA Patterns (with Example Problems)
   Pattern                                          Concept                                                 Example Questions
  1. Sliding Window                                Subarrays/substrings with                                Max sum subarray, Longest
                                                   conditions                                               substring without repeating chars

  2. Two Pointers                                  Sorted arrays, moving from ends                           Pair sum, Remove duplicates, Container
                                                                                                             with most water
  3. Fast & Slow Pointers                           Detect cycles, midpoints                                 Linked List cycle, Middle element
  4. Merge Intervals                                Combine overlapping intervals                            Merge intervals, Insert interval
  5. Cyclic Sort                                    Sorting numbers from range 1â€“N                           Find missing number, Find duplicate
  6. In-place Reversal of LinkedList                Reverse in subgroups                                     Reverse list, Reverse k-group
  7. Tree BFS                                       Level order traversal                                    Level order, Minimum depth
  8. Tree DFS                                       Recursive traversal                                      Path sum, Diameter of tree
  9. Two Heaps                                      Median, scheduling                                       Find median from stream
  10. Subsets / Backtracking                        Generate combinations                                    Subsets, Permutations, N-Queens
  11. Modified Binary Search                        Non-trivial searches                                     Search rotated array, Peak element
  12. Bit Manipulation                              XOR tricks                                               Single number, Missing number
  13. Dynamic Programming(DP)                       Overlapping subproblems                                  Knapsack, Longest Common Subsequence
  14. Top K Elements                                Use heap to find Kth                                     Kth largest, Top K frequent elements
  15. Graph BFS/DFS                                 Connectivity/pathfinding                                  Number of islands, Clone graph
  16. Union-Find (Disjoint Set)                     Connectivity groups                                      Redundant connection, Connected components
  17. Topological Sort                              Dependency ordering                                      Course schedule, Alien dictionary
  18. Trie / Prefix Tree                            String prefix problems                                   Word search, Autocomplete
  19. Greedy Algorithms                             Optimize step-by-step                                    Activity selection, Huffman coding
  20. Kadane / Prefix Sum                           Subarray sums                                            Maximum subarray, Subarray sum equals K

